17/07/2005
LONDON, Britain -- The EBRD said on Friday (15 July) it had given Montenegro an 11.5m-euro loan for road rehabilitation, the first such road sector credit extended by the Bank to the republic. The loan, which has a 15-year maturity and state guarantees by Serbia-Montenegro, is aimed at rebuilding important road networks and stabilising areas prone to landslides. (EBRD Web site - 15/07/05)
